---
import Icon from "~/components/Icon.svelte";
import BaseLayout from "~/layouts/BaseLayout.astro";

const description =
  "Noun gender, the seven cases, present-tense verb conjugation, and aspect. A short reference for reading the changed word endings in Serbian sentences.";
---

<BaseLayout pageTitle="Serbian grammar at a glance" description={description}>
  <article class="mx-auto w-full max-w-3xl px-6 py-16">
    <p class="mb-3 text-sm font-semibold uppercase tracking-[0.2em] text-accent">
      Grammar
    </p>
    <h1 class="text-4xl font-bold">Serbian grammar at a glance</h1>
    <p class="mt-4 max-w-2xl text-lg text-fg-muted">
      Bukvar teaches every word in its <strong class="text-fg"
        >dictionary form</strong
      >: nouns as you'd look them up, adjectives in the masculine singular, verbs
      in the infinitive. Serbian then changes a word's ending to show its role in
      a sentence, so a word often looks different in an example than it did on its
      flashcard.
    </p>
    <p class="mt-4 max-w-2xl text-lg text-fg-muted">
      These pages cover enough of that system to make sense of what you read.
      They're a reference, not a grammar course.
    </p>

    <div class="mt-10 grid gap-6 sm:grid-cols-2">
      <a
        href="/grammar/gender"
        class="rounded-xl border border-border bg-bg-elev p-6 hover:bg-primary-soft"
      >
        <h2 class="mb-2 flex items-center justify-between gap-2 text-lg font-semibold">
          Noun gender & the seven cases
          <Icon name="arrow-right" />
        </h2>
        <p class="text-sm leading-relaxed text-fg-muted">
          Why <span lang="sr">кафа</span> turns into <span lang="sr">кафу</span>,
          and <span lang="sr">град</span> into <span lang="sr">граду</span>. How
          to tell a noun's gender, what the seven cases do, and a full table of
          singular endings.
        </p>
      </a>

      <a
        href="/grammar/verbs"
        class="rounded-xl border border-border bg-bg-elev p-6 hover:bg-primary-soft"
      >
        <h2 class="mb-2 flex items-center justify-between gap-2 text-lg font-semibold">
          Verbs: present tense & aspect
          <Icon name="arrow-right" />
        </h2>
        <p class="text-sm leading-relaxed text-fg-muted">
          How <span lang="sr">радити</span> becomes <span lang="sr">радим</span>,
          <span lang="sr">радиш</span>, <span lang="sr">ради</span>. The three
          present-tense patterns, the common irregular verbs, and why Serbian
          often has two verbs where English has one.
        </p>
      </a>
    </div>

    <p class="mt-10 text-sm text-fg-muted">
      To practise the words themselves, <a
        href="/words"
        class="font-medium text-primary underline underline-offset-4 hover:text-primary-strong"
        >browse the word list</a
      > or <a
        href="/app"
        class="font-medium text-primary underline underline-offset-4 hover:text-primary-strong"
        >start a review session</a
      >.
    </p>
  </article>
</BaseLayout>
